BITSOM_BA_2511721 

Restaurant Menu & Order Management System

Overview

This project implements a Restaurant Order Management System using core Python data structures such as lists and dictionaries. The system performs menu exploration, cart operations, inventory tracking, and sales analysis.

Dataset Used

The assignment uses three main datasets:

Menu → Contains items, categories, prices, and availability
Inventory → Tracks stock levels and reorder thresholds
Sales Log → Stores daily orders and revenue details
Tasks Implemented
Task 1: Menu Exploration
Displayed menu grouped by category (Starters, Mains, Desserts)
Calculated:
Total items
Available items
Most expensive item
Items priced below ₹150
Task 2: Cart Operations
Implemented cart using list of dictionaries
Features:
Add items with validation
Prevent duplicate entries (update quantity instead)
Remove items from cart
Update item quantity
Simulated real order flow
Generated final bill with:
Subtotal
GST (5%)
Total payable
Task 3: Inventory Tracker
Used deep copy to preserve original inventory
Demonstrated difference between original and backup
Updated stock after order fulfillment
Handled insufficient stock cases
Generated reorder alerts for low stock items
Task 4: Sales Log Analysis
Calculated total revenue per day
Identified best-performing day
Found most frequently ordered item
Added new sales data dynamically
Displayed all orders using enumerate
Concepts Used
Dictionaries and nested dictionaries
Lists and list operations
Loops and conditional statements
Functions
Deep copy (copy.deepcopy)
String formatting
